  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators hypothesize that perioperative oral administration of pregabalin would
      reduce postoperative pain and produce reduction in postoperative opioid consumption after
      anterior cruciate ligament (ACL) reconstruction . Patients are randomly assign to 1 of 2
      groups. The placebo group receive placebo capsules 1 hour before surgery and 12 hours after
      initial dose. The pregabalin group receive pregabalin 150 mg, respectively at the same
      points.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
